article.headline: Chicago St. 78, Texas-Pan American 72
article.story: EDINBURG, Texas -- John Cantrell scored 28 points on 11-of-15 shooting to lead Chicago State past Texas-Pan American 78-72 on Saturday night. Tawrence Walton and Cantrell each hit two free throws in the final 10 seconds to preserve Chicago State's victory after Emmanuel Jones' dunk cut the lead to 74-72. Nick Weiermiller missed a 3-pointer for Texas-Pan American with nine seconds left. David Holston added 14 points for the Cougars (13-12). Carl Montgomery scored 12 and Tawrence Walton added 11. Jones led the Broncs (6-15) with 27 points on a 12-of-16 shooting performance. Julius Allgood scored 13 points off the bench and Nathan Hawkins added 10. Texas-Pan American outscored the Cougars in the paint 28-14, but gave up a 21-13 edge in points off turnovers.
